## ANALYZE (loop 3)

**Evidence:** authentication-history-extended (l-005) — 47 SSH attempts from 203.0.113.45 to prod-webserver-01 between 09:11:47Z–09:14:51Z (3m4s burst); 20 distinct usernames, all generic wordlist entries matching hydra/ncrack/patator defaults (admin, root, ubuntu, pi, oracle, postgres, deploy, git, jenkins, hadoop, tomcat, nagios, www-data, ansible, …); attempt rate 0.26/s; **zero** environment-specific names; **zero** successful auth events (rule 5501/5715) from 203.0.113.45 in the 10-min forward window (09:14:51Z–09:24:51Z).

**Assessment:**

- `?opportunistic-scanner`: `++` (was `+`) — pre-committed loop-3 refutation shape failed: shape was "usernames ≤2 distinct OR any env-specific name present." Observed 20 distinct names (far exceeds the ≤2 threshold) and zero environment-specific names (no `webapp-*`, `appuser-*`, `deploy-*`, or any naming pattern from the prod-webserver-01 application stack). Wordlist scatter matches documented default public tool wordlists verbatim. Attempt rate (0.26/s) and single-burst shape are consistent with automation, and the zero-success forward window confirms no foothold obtained. Named failed refutation: the ≤2-or-env-specific shape from HYPOTHESIZE loop 3 did not materialize.

- `?targeted-brute-force`: `--` (was `++` — loop 2 upgrade was unjustified; see Self-report) — pre-committed loop-3 refutation shape directly matched: "all usernames are generic wordlist entries with no environment-specific naming." All 20 observed usernames are generic; the cross-lead consistency note explicitly confirms zero env-specific names from the prod-webserver-01 stack. This is the core discriminating prediction of `?targeted-brute-force` (env-aware username selection), and it is directly falsified.

- `?credential-stuffing-external`: `--` (was `-`) — pre-committed loop-3 refutation shape matched on both prongs: (a) attempt rate 0.26/s is a mass-scanner profile, far exceeding the sub-0.05/s ceiling typical of credential-stuffing tools that slow-drip to evade rate limits; (b) usernames are purely generic wordlist entries, not real-looking personal identifiers or email-prefix patterns. Both prongs fire; refutation is complete.

- `?compromise-followup`: `--` (was live) — pre-committed loop-3 refutation shape met: zero rule-5501/5715 events from 203.0.113.45 to prod-webserver-01 or any other host in the 10-min forward window. Trust root reached (203.0.113.45 is an external endpoint; no accessible upstream).

**Surviving hypotheses:** `?opportunistic-scanner`

